          Product Information

          Pachisi Thayam Pagade is the national board game of India it is an ancient Indian board game. This is a two-four player strategy game. Other indian names for this game are chaupar, Chaupad, pagade, chausar, parcheesi, dayakattam, Sokkattan, Pagadi Pat. There is also a belief that this game may have been a precursor to the modern day board game-Ludo. Pagade is a race game in which two or four players can play. Winner: Four Mountain Thayam. The first player to get all his 4 pawns into the Home is the winner. Others can keep playing to get 1st runner-up, 2nd runner-up and the loser. In a partnership game, the team that first gets all its 8 pawns into Home is the winner. This product has been embroidered on cotton fabric. It includes wooden coins and Dices Pachikalu for playing. Suitable for adults and children over 5 years. Note: Cloth colour may vary, depending on the availability.

          • Age: 3 Years and above
          • Contents: 1 Set of Pachisi Traditional Board Game Set
          • Product Dimensions (approx): 8 cm (length) x 8 cm (width) x 6 cm (height)
          • Brand: Simple Days
          • Material: Cotton
          • Country of Origin: India
